New Delhi, Jul 14 (PTI) The Finance Ministry has received around 90 applications for the post of RBI Deputy Governor as S S Mundras three-year term is coming to end this month, an official said today. Some private bankers have also applied for the post as the position was open to private sector, a finance ministry official who did not wish to be identified said. About 90 applications are being scrutinised for the post of RBI Deputy Governor and the shortlisted name will be sent to Financial Sector Regulatory Appointment Search Committee (FSRASC) headed by Cabinet Secretary, the official said. A number of managing directors of public sector banks who met the criteria have applied as this position is reserved for a banker. 